# Sitemap + prerender script conventions

## Canonical host source of truth

- Read canonical host from `public/CNAME` when present.
- If absent, fallback to `package.json#homepage`.
- Do not hardcode `github.io` in scripts.

## Output expectations

- `scripts/generate-sitemap.mjs` must list **every indexable route**, including:
  - core pages (`/`, `/about/`, `/projects/`, `/articles/`, `/contact/`)
  - all project detail routes
  - all article routes (markdown + html)
  - static HTML pages like `/privacy-policy.html`
- Folder routes should be written with **trailing slashes**.

## SEO prerender expectations

- `scripts/generate-article-routes.mjs` should prerender **every `<loc>` in `build/sitemap.xml`** into `build/<path>/index.html` (skip real `.html` files).
- Each prerendered page must set:
  - `<title>`
  - `meta[name="description"]`
  - canonical link
  - `og:title`, `og:description`, `og:url`, `og:image`, `og:type`
  - `twitter:*` equivalents
  - JSON-LD via a deterministic `<script id="seo-ld-json" type="application/ld+json">...`

